com.fico.streamvar.api.model

Interface MergeableModelStep<I extends AbstractRecord,O extends AbstractRecord>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - Input record type
    O - Output record type
    All Superinterfaces:
    ModelStep<I,O>

    public interface MergeableModelStep<I extends AbstractRecord,O extends AbstractRecord>
extends ModelStep<I,O>
    Interface for a kind of ModelStep that updates or querying mergeable profile records in a possibly multi-step model. Concrete implementations of this interface must include a public no-args constructor.

    • Method Detail

      • isMergeNeeded

        boolean isMergeNeeded(MergeableProfileRecord profile,
                      I record)
        This method is called by the runtime platform to determine whether a particular MergeableProfileRecord should be merged or not during a particular transaction. This method will be called after the ModelStep.getProfileKeys(AbstractRecord) method and before the ModelStep.calculate(CalculableProfileRecords, AbstractRecord) method. If getProfileKeys returned multiple MergeableProfileRecords, then this method will be called once for each such profile.
        Parameters:
        profile - The profile that we are considering
        record - The current incoming record to this model step
        Returns:
        True if the profile should be merged, false otherwise

      • merge

        MergeableProfileRecord merge(MergeableProfileRecord targetProfile,
                             List<MergeableProfileRecord> otherProfiles,
                             I record)
        Performs the merge of profiles into the passed profile (will be the MergeableProfileRecord from getProfileKeys). Will be called for each type of MergeableProfileRecord, in the order they appear in getProfileKeys.
        Parameters:
        targetProfile - the target profile
        otherProfiles - other profiles
        record - the current incoming record to this model step
        Returns:
        a mergeable profile record
